  "title": "Senior / Technical Service Engineer (Chemical )",
  "description": "<p>1.    Monitoring and troubleshooting current chemical programs through plant data analysis, laboratory results and communicating the same to relevant personnel (Clients\n  and within company)</p><p>2.    Respond to Clients clarifications / concerns in a timely manner and escalating to manager, if necessary, to ensure customer satisfaction.</p><p>3.    Value additional proposition and initiatives for customers</p><p>4.    Identify new business opportunities and assist in pursue and gathering information and preparation of reports.</p><p>5.    Prepare troubleshooting and finding reports for any incidents happen. </p><p>6.    Engaging with clients on proposing improvement plans to the units for operational excellence through reliability and safety.</p><p>7.    Share findings with technical team to discuss on arising concerns and seeking solution from them.</p><p>8.    Discussion and coordination with technical team for new programs and KPI achievement </p><p>9.    Oversee inventory and delivery planning for Customer to prevent disruption to operations.</p><p>10.  Assist in technical monitoring/analysis/troubleshooting of other\n  programs where applicable</p><p>11.  Timely submission and improvement to customer’s daily/monthly monitoring\n  reports.</p><p>12.  Co-ordinate with Site technicians on site activities in ensuring\n  HSSE compliance and housekeeping. </p>",
